The Brno-based company developing CCV software is facing legal action from Finnish telecommunications equipment manufacturer Nokia. The Finns do not like the fact that the brno warehouse management company's program is called Lokia WMS, E15 newspaper reported. Nokia therefore objected to lokia's application to the Industrial Property Office. The CCV resents that subdiching is unlikely.
Marketing Director Petr Ondrášek said that two dozen customers have been using the program since last September.
